# UX style — Build Pa'l Norte

## No decorative icons on labels

Do **not** put small Lucide (or similar) icons before section eyebrows, `SectionLabel`, field labels, or stat/meta labels.

These read as tacky decoration and clutter the hierarchy. Typography and tracking carry the label — that is enough.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — icon prefixes a section eyebrow
<span className="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 ...">
  <Shirt size={12} />
  {copy.label}
</span>

<SectionLabel icon={<PencilIcon />}>{labels.editSection}</SectionLabel>

// ✅ GOOD — text-only label
<span className="text-[10px] font-black tracking-[0.28em] ...">
  {copy.label}
</span>

<SectionLabel>{labels.editSection}</SectionLabel>
```

Use `SectionLabel` from `@/components/platform` for card section headers. It does not accept an `icon` prop.

## Where icons are fine

Icons belong when they **communicate action or state**, not decoration:

- **Buttons and links** — e.g. `PlatformLinkButton`, sign-out, CTA arrows
- **Status chips** — e.g. checkmark on “Saved: M”
- **Empty states / avatars / list row affordances** — when the icon is the primary content
- **Nav and toolbar** — language switcher, menu items

When unsure: if removing the icon changes nothing about what the user can *do* or *understand*, leave it out.

## Eyebrow / label styling

- Uppercase micro-labels: `text-[9px]`–`text-[10px]`, `font-black`, wide tracking (`tracking-[0.22em]`–`tracking-[0.28em]`)
- Muted on dark UI: `text-white/25` (platform) or `text-[#aaff00]/90` (landing accent sections)
- Prefer `SectionLabel` + rule line over one-off icon+text combos
